<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="no"?><?Xpress productLine="ncc-clause" ?><clause xmlns:xt="urn:xpressauthor:trackchanges" id="_cab53ca9-747e-4dde-b73a-b06a1aa551ff" outputclass="ncc-clause"><meta><facet building="Class 1a"/><facet building="Class 1b"/><facet building="Class 5"/><facet building="Class 6"/><facet building="Class 7a"/><facet building="Class 7b"/><facet building="Class 8"/><facet building="Class 9a"/><facet building="Class 9b"/><facet building="Class 9c"/><facet building="Class 10a"/><facet building="Class 10b"/><facet building="Class 10c"/></meta><sptc>F6D4</sptc><title id="_20fe8417-7b2a-41f2-b77b-a28ef1a2c24d">Natural light borrowed from adjoining room</title><archive-num>2019: F4.3</archive-num><subclause id="_38832a52-7377-495c-a62c-f1902024acca" outputclass="subclause"><title id="_ac110bd2-d892-4ce2-bca6-554699353e43">SubClause</title><num>1</num><p>Natural light to a room in a Class 2 building or Class 4 part of a building or in a <xref format="dita" href="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/5e2c1f63-e589-4ce1-95e8-5c3e286a7aff/1473_0.4.0.xml#_d2c89488-8a36-464b-94f6-a91d0f5a6c9c" id="_ec1753b3-ca11-40ca-bb0c-58d93e50e366" scope="local" type="abcb-glossentry">sole-occupancy unit</xref> of a Class 3 building, may come through one or more glazed panels or openings from an adjoining room (including an enclosed verandah) if—</p><ol outputclass="alpha"><li id="_e101050d-ef60-42c5-99c9-18c8571a7428">both rooms are within the same <xref format="dita" href="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/5e2c1f63-e589-4ce1-95e8-5c3e286a7aff/1473_0.4.0.xml#_d2c89488-8a36-464b-94f6-a91d0f5a6c9c" id="_488d4ecc-6dbc-4e57-a959-ae70739f1649" scope="local" type="abcb-glossentry">sole-occupancy unit</xref> or the enclosed verandah is on common property; and</li><li id="_7fecf617-e02a-4290-af83-094c90e6afe8">the glazed panels or openings have an aggregate light transmitting area of not less than 10% of the <xref format="dita" href="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/5e2c1f63-e589-4ce1-95e8-5c3e286a7aff/1314_2.10.0.xml#_7da927fe-453e-424f-b6ec-280f4e464397" id="_d849e703-c8e8-4c27-91e3-942df3e93a4c" scope="local" type="abcb-glossentry">floor area</xref> of the room to which it provides light; and</li><li id="_970d09c5-1213-40e6-ae1d-f3c4c8b20081">the adjoining room has—<ol><li><xref format="dita" href="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/5e2c1f63-e589-4ce1-95e8-5c3e286a7aff/1525_29.1.0.xml#_48631093-d96b-4a40-a86d-7ffae028f24d" id="_986fb939-183f-47e8-8a8b-fcf7737455aa" scope="local" type="abcb-glossentry">windows</xref>, excluding <xref format="dita" href="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/5e2c1f63-e589-4ce1-95e8-5c3e286a7aff/1441_5.5.0.xml#_12b88f11-1c3d-4d91-bc65-02588a4dc524" id="_6195277e-0925-4834-b90a-8758772a9b1f" scope="local" type="abcb-glossentry">roof lights</xref>, that—<ol><li>have an aggregate light transmitting area of not less than 10% of the combined <xref format="dita" href="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/5e2c1f63-e589-4ce1-95e8-5c3e286a7aff/1314_2.10.0.xml#_7da927fe-453e-424f-b6ec-280f4e464397" id="_eb26411c-f553-413e-9152-cad6a25fcb2d" scope="local" type="abcb-glossentry">floor areas</xref> of both rooms; and</li><li>are open to the sky or face a court or other space open to the sky or an open verandah, carport or the like; or</li></ol></li><li><xref format="dita" href="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/5e2c1f63-e589-4ce1-95e8-5c3e286a7aff/1441_5.5.0.xml#_12b88f11-1c3d-4d91-bc65-02588a4dc524" id="_759450bb-787c-4cc5-b679-6e0b1c237e3e" scope="local" type="abcb-glossentry">roof lights</xref>, that—<ol><li>have an aggregate light transmitting area of not less than 3% of the combined <xref format="dita" href="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/5e2c1f63-e589-4ce1-95e8-5c3e286a7aff/1314_2.10.0.xml#_7da927fe-453e-424f-b6ec-280f4e464397" id="_015a6eed-c51b-40fe-809a-5c01df58b6af" scope="local" type="abcb-glossentry">floor areas</xref> of both rooms; and</li><li>are open to the sky; or</li></ol></li><li>a proportional combination of <xref format="dita" href="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/5e2c1f63-e589-4ce1-95e8-5c3e286a7aff/1525_29.1.0.xml#_48631093-d96b-4a40-a86d-7ffae028f24d" id="_61139de4-cede-4692-9c33-68e4f21375ec" scope="local" type="abcb-glossentry">windows</xref> and <xref format="dita" href="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/5e2c1f63-e589-4ce1-95e8-5c3e286a7aff/1441_5.5.0.xml#_12b88f11-1c3d-4d91-bc65-02588a4dc524" id="_d29269ff-a423-4919-93b8-8fad70f89a84" scope="local" type="abcb-glossentry">roof lights</xref> <xref format="dita" href="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/5e2c1f63-e589-4ce1-95e8-5c3e286a7aff/1432_4.0.0.xml#_af6fde9f-147d-4782-8b85-42044e80fd42" id="_6fabf30c-30ce-4c9e-9caa-8dbc7393941d" scope="local" type="abcb-glossentry">required</xref> by (i) and (ii).</li></ol></li></ol></subclause><subclause id="_552ae264-0435-4b1c-b5f2-0eb1346876da" outputclass="subclause"><title id="_b20d55e4-b481-48da-a4b3-224710b6725e">SubClause</title><num>2</num><p>The areas specified in (1)(b) and (c) may be reduced as appropriate if direct natural light is provided from another source.</p></subclause></clause>